  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>15 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to try the algorithms they saw earlier in the lesson. The important thing is that they combine hundreds and hundreds, tens and tens, and ones and ones, which should be a familiar idea from grade 2. The synthesis provides an opportunity to show a different way of recording newly composed tens and hundreds when compositions are required, which will be discussed in more detail in subsequent lessons. Provide access to base-ten blocks for students to use to support their reasoning about the algorithms, in case requested.</p>
<p>Students analyze and improve a given explanation of how to find a sum, filling in details and using more precise language to explain the calculation more fully (MP3, MP6).</p>
<p>This activity uses <em>MLR3 Clarify, Critique, Correct</em>. <em>Advances: reading, writing, representing</em></p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[mmmmmmmmmm]</p>
    <!-- si hay materiales, crear los archivos -mat.ptx (para materiales de la actividad) y -matCentros.ptx (para mencionar los otros centros que se usan y para los que se necesitan materiales) y poner los materiales ahí usando los archivos de template. Después hacer xinclude  de estos archivos en la lista de materiales de la lección.-->
    <!-- <xi:include href="./act-probarUnAlgoritmo-mat.ptx"/>  -->
    <!-- <xi:include href="./act-probarUnAlgoritmo-matCentros.ptx"/>  -->
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
      <li>Give students access to base-ten blocks.</li>
      <li>
        <q>Ahora vamos a tener la oportunidad de probar los algoritmos que Lin y Han usaron en la actividad anterior</q>  // Now you are going to have a chance to try the algorithms that Lin and Han used in the last activity. Take a minute to think about which algorithm you want to use for each problem.
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: quiet think time</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li> Con su pareja, prueben un algoritmo para encontrar el valor de cada suma // 
        <q>Work with your partner to try an algorithm to find the value of each sum.</q>
      </li>
      <li>5 minutes: partner work time</li>
      <li>Monitor for students who use Lin’s algorithm and Han's algorithm on the last problem.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


